  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Maria Weston Chapman writes mostly about family affairs. She gives instructions about a bill, urges her daughter to have a certain room in her house cleaned, and tells her granddaughter Anne to write French. Chapman writes: &quot;Beg Laugel to write to me.&quot; She mentions someone named Harriet. She says that Mrs. Bates plans to come to Liverpool.</subfield>
